# Design system (Pulse UI)

## Stats and pagination

**Never compute aggregate stats from the current page only.** Stats (totals, counts) must come from the backend (full dataset). Display the stats object the API returns; don't derive totals from `items.length` of the paginated list.

## Entity/platform colors

**Platform/entity colors are static (identity), not status-based.** e.g. Android = green, iOS = blue always. Communicate status via **variant** (filled/outline/light), **opacity**, or tooltips, not by changing the entity's color.

## Border radius

Use a consistent system: e.g. `radius="md"` for containers (Card, Paper), `radius="sm"` for elements (Button, Badge, Input). Don't mix random radius values.

## Error states

Error UI must be **action-oriented**: icon + single clear message + **Retry** (or other recovery) button. Use Paper/Card for layout. No redundant title+message; no close (X) button as the only action. See `error-handling.mdc`.

## Color palette (B2B)

Prefer professional colors: **blue** primary actions, **gray** secondary, **green** success, **orange** warning, **red** error. Avoid playful colors (grape, pink, violet, lime) for primary UI. Pulse UI uses a teal theme in places (see Session Replay QUICK_REFERENCE).

## Button hierarchy

Use consistent variants in a column/section: e.g. one primary (filled), rest outline or light. Don't mix unrelated colors/variants for the same action type.

## Mantine and styles

Use Mantine components (Button, Paper, Group, Stack, Table, etc.) and `@tabler/icons-react`. Use CSS modules (`*.module.css`) for screen-specific layout. See `.cursor/TECH_STACK_PRACTICES.md` and theme in `src/theme/`.

## Accessibility

Semantic HTML; labels for form controls; ARIA where it adds clarity. Error and loading states should be understandable and actionable.
